(he apologized, it only happened once, no biggie)<br>
<br>
Game, set and match rockhoppers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I get ported back to PoK and call out for a ressurection (I can happily accept 70% or more and usually pay the same whether its a 70 or a 96. I am just glad to regain some xp.)<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I get a tell from a cleric, a deal is struck for 200pp and we are on our way.<br>
<br>
The cleric (whose name I unfortunately have forgotten) thought the payment so acceptable that I even recieved a Virtue with the deal. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now, I knew my companion had also contacted a cleric for a ress and so I sent her a tell to check the status.<br>
<br>
And here is my beef:<br>
<br>
She had been chewed out by the cleric for not offering enough money, had in fact been told that people usually offered between 400-1000pp and she had more or less been told to &quot;get in line&quot; as far as I understood it.<br>
<br>
Now, I understand that the price can go up if the cleric has to run long ways, have to zone a lot, be exposed to dangers and so on. In some places up to a thousand plat might be justified...but this was Dawnshroud peaks and we were ready to drag corpses to the entrance!<br>
<br>
Is there somewhere a &quot;hidden list&quot; of prices that one should be aware of? In my mind i figured that I offered a price, a bit of bargaining takes place and then a deal was struck or I had to search for a new Cleric if a price could not be found that satisfied both of us.<br>
<br>
Have I misunderstood anything, have we came across a &quot;bad cleric&quot;, or is there indeed, a form of &quot;inofficial&quot; price list?<br>
<br>
<br>
In the end it turned out well though and my companion got a ress. (Due to a misunderstanding on my part the cleric that ressed me had already left for adventure)<br>
Thank you very much to cleric Ironheart of guild Tribulation for ressing my companion, buffing her <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and then declining payment.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
