<br>
Not everybody is required to do the same, of course.  Everyone has the right to decide for themselves what their time and energy are worth to them.  If they don't want to help you out at all, that's their right and their decision, even if you over them 20,000pp.<br>
<br>
The only thing is trying to make a person feel bad either way.  If someone says &quot;No way that offer sucks, I'm not wasting my time coming out to rezz you for less than 400pp LOL!&quot; that's just mean and stupid.  Likewise, it would be equally lame for someone to continuously demand that someone come out and help them after their offer has been refused.<br>
<br>
What a rezz is worth to a person (both on the receiving and the giving end) will vary.  There is no &quot;standard market value&quot; to go by on rezzes, no formula, official or unofficial to work it out.  Personally I tend to keep 150pp on me at all times, and that's what I usually tend to offer a person to rezz me. <p>--Velsor<br>
